      "message": "I think there\u0027s another step that could make this all more user friendly: The hook function get passed here as a pointer to a func like\n\ntemplate\u003ctypename Inputs, typename ExtraData\u003e\nusing DataHookFn \u003d  void(const GrGLSLProgramDataManager\u0026 pdman, const GrGLSLSkSLFP\u0026 glslProc, const Inputs\u0026 inputs, const ExtraData\u0026 extraData);\n\nMake takes a DataHookFn\u003cInputs, ExtraData\u003e* hookFn param.\n\nYou could type-erase it by having the GrSkSLFP/GrGLSLSkFP take a pointer to this function type:\nvoid(const GrGLSLProgramDataManager\u0026 pdman,\n     const GrGLSLSkSLFP\u0026 glslProc,\n     const void* inputs\n     const void* extraData);\n\nwhich you define locally here as:\n\nauto genericFn \u003d [] (const GrGLSLProgramDataManager\u0026 pdman,\n                     const GrGLSLSkSLFP\u0026 glslProc,\n                     const void* inputs\n                     const void* extraData) {\n   (*hookFn)(pdman, glslProc, *reinterpret_cast\u003cconst Inputs*\u003e(inputs), *reinterpret_cast\u003cconst ExtraData*\u003e(extraData));\n};",
